huawei.name: huawei
huawei.description: This MIB defines the managed objects that are used by the function interfaces of the SNMP Northbound Interface.

thirdNMSFaultFilter.name: thirdNMSFaultFilter
thirdNMSFaultFilter.description: IP:Port:AlarmLevelFilter:AlarmCategoryFilter AlarmLevelFilter = xxxx (Critical, Major, Minor, Warning) (1 - filter, 0 - report) AlarmCategoryFilter = yyyyyy (Event, Fault, Recovery, Acknowledge, UnAcknowledge, Change) (1 - filter, 0 - report) Both AlarmLevelFilter and AlarmCategoryFilter are optional and both or any one can be set E.g.: 10.18.17.28:9999:0110:100000 Only events of major and minor severity will be send to the OSS [10.18.17.28:9999] and rest filtered. The format to specify only AlarmLevelFilter is: 10.18.17.28:9999:0110 The format to specify only AlarmCategoryFilter is: 10.18.17.28:9999::100000 Get attempt on this node will result in error.

hwNmClearAlarms.name: hwNmClearAlarms
hwNmClearAlarms.description: This provides the functionality of clearing alarms to third party NMS. The alarms can be cleared based on alarm serial number. Multiple serial numbers are separated by comma(,). Alarms serial number(s)are of type unsigned long and incompatible types are automatically considered as invalid serial number(s). Get attempt on this node will result in error. Output: Serial number(s) of alarms which could not be cleared. This also contains Alarm serial number(s) with incorrect syntax. If all alarms are successfully cleared then output is blank.

hwNmAcknowledgeAlarms.name: hwNmAcknowledgeAlarms
hwNmAcknowledgeAlarms.description: This provides the functionality of acknowledging alarms to third party NMS. The alarms can be acknowledged based on alarm serial number. Multiple serial numbers are separated by comma(,). Alarms serial number(s) are of type unsigned long and incompatible types are automatically considered as invalid serial number(s). Get attempt on this node will result in error. Output: Serial number(s) of alarms which could not be acknowledged. This also contains Alarm serial number(s) with incorrect syntax. If all alarms are successfully acknowledged then output is blank.

hwNmUnAcknowledgeAlarms.name: hwNmUnAcknowledgeAlarms
hwNmUnAcknowledgeAlarms.description: This provides the functionality of unacknowledging alarms to third party NMS. The alarms can be unacknowledged based on alarm serial number. Multiple serial numbers are separated by comma(,). Alarms serial number(s) are of type unsigned long and incompatible types are automatically considered as invalid serial number(s). Get attempt on this node will result in error. Output: Serial number(s) of alarms which could not be unacknowledged. This also contains Alarm serial number(s) with incorrect syntax. If all alarms are successfully unacknowledged then output is blank.

hwNmNorthboundEventSynchronizationComman.name: hwNmNorthboundEventSynchronizationCommandStart
hwNmNorthboundEventSynchronizationComman.description: This node is to be set to start the alarm synchronization. The format to query alarms is:- IP:port:start time:end time Query time can be UTC time, Local time or Local time with timezone. Syntax for start time and end time is - YYYYMMDDhhmmss. The interpretation of the start time and end time depends on 'AlarmTimeFormat' parameter in $IMAP_ROOT/etc/conf/snmpsvc.xml file. Query can be in any of the following formats: 1. Local time(AlarmTimeFormat = 0): Format:- IP:port:start time:end time Here, the start time and end time will be considered to be in local time format. 2. UTC time(AlarmTimeFormat = 1): Format:- IP:port:start time:end time Here, the start time and end time will be considered to be UTC format. 3. Local time with timezone(AlarmTimeFormat = 2): Format:- IP:port:start time:end time:timezone:dstflag Here, the user can mention the timezone and dst flag. Format to mention timezone is +/-hh.mm if dstflag is 0 - DST disabled, 1- DST enabled. Format to omit dst flag:- IP:port:start time:end time:timezone, will consider the dstflag to be 0. The agent will send alarm synchronization result to the IP and port specified which were raised between start time and end time. If start time and end time are missing all alarms are reported. Start time and end time both are optional. If end time is missing current time of the EMS is taken as end time. If end time is present start time is not optional, it means you cannot provide end time without specifying the start time. If there is already a running alarm synchronization for that IP and port,it will return a commit fail error.

hwNmNorthboundEventSynchronizationComman.name: hwNmNorthboundEventSynchronizationCommandStop
hwNmNorthboundEventSynchronizationComman.description: This node is to be set to stop the alarm synchronization. It should be set as NMS's IP:port,and the agent will stop alarm synchronization for the IP and port specified. If alarm synchronization is not in progress for the specified IP and port,it will return a commit fail error.
